1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,730
Three, walk 25% faster.

2
00:00:04,159 --> 00:00:08,690
When I was a youngster, just going to the county seat was a big treat.

3
00:00:08,879 --> 00:00:12,610
After all the errands were accomplished and we were back in the car,

4
00:00:12,719 --> 00:00:19,010
my mother would often say, Davy, let's just sit here a while and watch the people walk by.

5
00:00:19,679 --> 00:00:22,210
Mother was an excellent game player.

6
00:00:22,319 --> 00:00:24,530
She'd say, see that fellow?

7
00:00:24,719 --> 00:00:27,010
What do you suppose is troubling him?

8
00:00:27,119 --> 00:00:31,010
Or what do you think that lady there is going to do?

9
00:00:31,119 --> 00:00:35,489
or, look at that person, he just seems to be in a fog.

10
00:00:36,159 --> 00:00:39,889
Watching people walk and move about became real fun.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,810
It was a lot cheaper than the movies, which was one of the reasons,

12
00:00:43,839 --> 00:00:48,929
I learned later, that Mother developed the game, and it was a lot more instructive.

13
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:51,570
I still am a walk-watcher.

14
00:00:51,679 --> 00:01:01,489
In corridors, lobbies, on sidewalks, I still occasionally find myself studying human behavior simply by watching people move about.

15
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:11,489
Psychologists link slovenly posture and sluggish walking to unpleasant attitudes toward oneself, work, and the people around us.

16
00:01:11,839 --> 00:01:19,889
But psychologists also tell us you can actually change your attitudes by changing your posture and speed of movement.

17
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:24,929
Watch, and you discover that body action is the result of mind action.

18
00:01:25,279 --> 00:01:31,090
The extremely beaten people, the real down-and-outers, just shuffle and stumble along.

19
00:01:31,199 --> 00:01:33,489
They have zero self-confidence.

20
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,849
Average people have the average walk.

21
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:38,929
Their pace is average.

22
00:01:39,119 --> 00:01:43,810
They have the look of, I really don't have very much pride in myself.

23
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,290
Then there's a third group.

24
00:01:46,399 --> 00:01:49,409
Persons in this group show super confidence.

25
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,650
They walk faster than the average.

26
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:54,929
There seems to be a slight sprint in the way they walk.

27
00:01:55,199 --> 00:02:01,010
Their walk tells the world, I've got some place important to go, something important to do.

28
00:02:01,199 --> 00:02:06,130
What's more, I will succeed at what I will do fifteen minutes from now.

29
00:02:06,639 --> 00:02:11,810
Use the walk 25% faster technique to help build self-confidence.

30
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:19,489
Throw your shoulders back, lift up your head, move ahead just a little faster, and feel self-confidence grow.

31
00:02:19,839 --> 00:02:21,570
Just try and see.

